This project also helped in understanding practical challenges such as handling file permissions in Docker environments, managing environment variables, and debugging containerized applications. During the implementation, issues related to file access permissions were encountered when generating output files inside Docker containers. These issues were resolved by properly configuring user permissions and volume mappings. The project also emphasized the importance of modular code design, where different layers such as service, model, and utility were separated to ensure maintainability and scalability. Logging was incorporated to track execution flow and assist in debugging. The use of Docker ensured that the application could be easily deployed and executed across different systems without dependency issues. Overall, the project enhanced understanding of backend development, data simulation techniques, and container-based deployment strategies.
